<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="656" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d656">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/10–1050</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-10">October 10, 1950</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p rend="center">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Conversation With Mr. Lovett</hi>
                    </p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Siberian Bombing</p>
                    <p>The Pentagon has sent a very stiff message to General Stratemeyer directing a
                        report within 48 hours, which would be tomorrow night, and, in the event
                        that the bombing did take place, directing that the commanding officer
                        responsible should be removed. Mr. Lovett thinks well of further orders
                        making clear our original intention that ail our planes on operational
                        missions should keep a long way away from the border.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>